cs.LO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.PL 

The paper deals with the problem of supervisory control for a class of discrete event systems modelled by fuzzy automata. This involves the use of fuzzy languages and the extension of the concept of discrete event system controllability by incorporating fuzziness. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories.
